Class SensorEntry

java.lang.Object
sep4.iot.gateway.model.SensorEntry
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class SensorEntry
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
SensorEntry object is the container for the data received from Loriot as an uplink and data to be sent to Loriot as a downlink

      Constructor used when getting Sensor entries from the client in order to construct a new downlink message
      Parameters:
      entry_key - - unique entry key of the sensor entry
      hardware_id - - unique hex identification string for the hardware
      user_key - - unique user identification number
      entry_time - - the entry time of the sensor entry
      air_temperature - - measured air temperature
      air_humidity - - measured air humidity
      air_co2 - - measured air co2 value
      light_level - - measured light level
      desired_air_temperature - - desired value for the air temperature
      desired_air_humidity - - desired value for the air humidity
      desired_air_co2 - - desired value for the co2 level
      desired_light_level - - desired value for the light level
